  "commentary": "With SPX at 6821.82 sitting below the GEX flip at 6847, dealers are long gamma and will hedge by selling any rallies toward the massive 6850-6900 resistance zone where they hold 5.7B in positive gamma. The thick wall of positive gamma from 6850-7000 creates a natural ceiling, while the negative gamma pocket at 6700 provides downside support where dealers would aggressively buy dips. Current positioning suggests dealers will fade moves in either direction, with particular selling pressure expected if SPX challenges the 6900 max gamma strike.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 6700-6900 with dealers capping upside moves.",
